lines.text: Well, we finished earlier tonight than I expected.
You and your Scotland Yard. If it weren't for Edgar Wallace, nobody'd ever heard of it.
Detectives in glass houses shouldn't wave clues.
You haven't seen "Finger Prints." I'd like to see that. Uh, still, it's about Scotland Yard. Might be amusing. They're bound to get all the details wrong.
I don't see why. I did hear they got a real criminal to direct it, so as to be on the safe side.
Did she tell you who did it?
You want to look out. She'll be losing your job, my boy. I say, I suppose we should soon have lady detectives up at the Yard, eh? And I should be all right out the door, won't I?
And as I was saying and always will say - knives is not right!
